CourseInformation.objects.create(course_administrator=CourseAdminstrator.objects.get(admin_id='CH'), course_name='環境工程(一)', course_teacher='蔡伸隆', course_type=0, course_discription='因應環境議題的發展與變化，本課程將系統化介紹水環境之議題，以及相對應的工程技術的應用，目的在提供本校三四年級學生環境工程入門。本課程著重水與廢水處理技術之介紹。除了水文循環、水質分析、與水質管理，自來水工程將介紹主要處理單元，包括混凝、膠凝、沉澱、過濾、消毒等；廢水工程則介紹生物處理程序、污泥處理與處置、污水回收與再利用等，最後以永續水資源利用為總結。課程中主要探討水與廢水處理技術之物理、化學、微生物原理，並學習初步工程設計，以作為未來從事環境工程之專業基礎。<br>In face of emerging environmental issues, local, regional, and global ones, this course aims to introduce engineering control strategies for junior and senior students with chemical engineering background. Wastewater treatment technologies are the focuses. Topics will include water resource engineering, water quality analysis and management, wastewater treatment, sludge treatment and disposal, and water reuse. Major unit processes, physical, chemical and biological, in wastewater treatment will be introduced covering membrane bioreactor, aerobic, and anaerobic processes. Treatment and disposal of activated sludge and water reuse will also be included. The course will be summarized in the last chapter of sustainable water management. Basic physical, chemical, and biological principles will be introduced as well as some design practice. At least one filed trip will be arranged. Three adjunct professors from outside will be invited to share their experiences with students.', course_website='http://info.ntust.edu.tw/faith/edua/app/qry_linkoutline.aspx?semester=1071&courseno=CH3413301')
CourseInformation.objects.create(course_administrator=CourseAdminstrator.objects.get(admin_id='CH'), course_name='印刷電路板及封裝技術', course_teacher='未  定', course_type=1, course_discription='課程包括印刷電路板之應用、光罩技術、鑽孔之鍍銅、蝕銅、多層板之製造、錫銲、表面粘著技術、厚膜及薄膜技術、線路聯結、熱傳導及可靠性。//Electronic circuits in industry are normally manufactured through the use of PCBs (Printed Circuit Boards). The boards are made from glass reinforced plastic with copper tracks in the place of wires. In this class, we’ll discuss the composition of a printed circuit board, cover some terminology, a look at methods of assembly, and discuss briefly the design process behind creating a new PCB. The following subjects will be involved in the course:<br>1.Introduction of PCB/TPCA<br>2.Basic PCB MFG Introduction<br>3.Requirements and specifics of PCB<br>4.Relationship between electrical charaterization and Design of PCB<br>5.Multi-layers and High Density PCB <br>6.Dielectrics material of Multi-Layers PCB<br>7.Design and Synthesis of Multi-Layers PCB<br>8.Flexible PCB<br>9.Composition for Flexible PCB<br>10.Structure, fabrication and design of flexible PCB<br>11.Applications of flexible PCB', course_website='http://info.ntust.edu.tw/faith/edua/app/qry_linkoutline.aspx?semester=1071&courseno=CH3507701')
