CourseInformation.objects.create(course_administrator=CourseAdminstrator.objects.get(admin_id='FL'), course_name='批判識能：問題導向式寫作 (一)', course_teacher='駱藝瑄', course_type=0, course_discription='本課程旨在幫助學生以批判識能的角度，瞭解學術英文組織架構、以及各類型文體之組成要素與特色。本課程將引導學生以問題為導向的視角，認識各層級寫作的標準與所應具備的知識與能力 (ACTFL Writing Proficiency Guidelines) ，協助學生將寫作理論應用在個人和小組問題導向寫作任務中，並與閱讀課程結合，進行多模態創意寫作 (如行銷廣告、文宣、書籍、影片等)，邀請相關業界點評，擴增並深化寫作經驗。學生也將搭配並應用寫作軟體，審視自己與同儕的寫作作品，反覆練習及改寫，培養評論寫作的基礎，增進寫作知識和經驗，提升寫作能力與技巧。', course_website='http://info.ntust.edu.tw/faith/edua/app/qry_linkoutline.aspx?semester=1071&courseno=FL2051301')
CourseInformation.objects.create(course_administrator=CourseAdminstrator.objects.get(admin_id='FL'), course_name='批判識能：問題導向式寫作 (一)', course_teacher='駱藝瑄', course_type=0, course_discription='本課程旨在幫助學生以批判識能的角度，瞭解學術英文組織架構、以及各類型文體之組成要素與特色。本課程將引導學生以問題為導向的視角，認識各層級寫作的標準與所應具備的知識與能力 (ACTFL Writing Proficiency Guidelines) ，協助學生將寫作理論應用在個人和小組問題導向寫作任務中，並與閱讀課程結合，進行多模態創意寫作 (如行銷廣告、文宣、書籍、影片等)，邀請相關業界點評，擴增並深化寫作經驗。學生也將搭配並應用寫作軟體，審視自己與同儕的寫作作品，反覆練習及改寫，培養評論寫作的基礎，增進寫作知識和經驗，提升寫作能力與技巧。', course_website='http://info.ntust.edu.tw/faith/edua/app/qry_linkoutline.aspx?semester=1071&courseno=FL2051302')
CourseInformation.objects.create(course_administrator=CourseAdminstrator.objects.get(admin_id='FL'), course_name='批判識能：問題導向式閱讀 (一)', course_teacher='楊智琄', course_type=0, course_discription='此課程宗旨有四：1. 擴展並精進閱讀各種文體之能力，如以古典文學小說、現代小說為基底，進而廣泛閱讀時事論述、演講文本、至產業分析報導等篇章。2. 以問題解決為導向之閱讀計畫, 如社會、世界、人類等議題，密切結合閱讀、思辨、闡述與辯論等技能。3. 以寫作表達閱讀與思辨過程，經由結構性寫作，同時反思與自我檢視閱讀過程的理解、挑戰、及尋找解答之所有階段與歷程。最後，4. 結合業界合作創意文案設計、翻譯、與撰寫。學生將有機會大量閱讀各類商業品牌背後故事、來源、成因等資料，閱讀中英文文案紀錄，並進行”設計思維”與”創意寫作”之練習。目的就是培養學生高階批判思考、自我學習、與精準豐富之表達能力。<br>Four purposes are aimed at: 1) To broaden and sharpen students’ ability in reading different genres, e.g. classic literature, contemporary fiction, and based on which students proceed with extensively reading essays and arguments on social issues, about the world, and in humanity related topics, speech scripts, as well as analytical reports on current industries. 2) To read for deeply understanding a problem/issue and then to propose solutions and conclusions, integrating other practices and training in critical thinking, illustrating and arguing skills. 3) To express one’s voice and ideas after reading and thinking through structured writing while reflecting and examining one’s own trajectory along which comprehension is reached, challenges overcome, and answers discovered. 4) To read into professional domains so as to learn creative copy writing and translation. To do so, students are going to collect and read extensive documents in both English and Chinese on well-known brands of commodities that have stories introducing and promoting them. Lecturers from the private sectors will be invited to co-teach and give training sessions on “design thinking” and “creative writing.” The goal', course_website='http://info.ntust.edu.tw/faith/edua/app/qry_linkoutline.aspx?semester=1071&courseno=FL2053301')
